{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/code/eslint-for-gatsby-howto","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<ol>\n<li>Check that you have <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">ESLint extension</a> installed.</li>\n<li>(Optional) While you are playing with linters and VS Code extensions, you can think about a <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=DavidAnson.vscode-markdownlint\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">linter for Markdown</a> files.</li>\n<li>Install required npm development packages</li>\n<li>Edit the config file</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"npm-packages\" style=\"position:relative;\">npm packages<a href=\"#npm-packages\" aria-label=\"npm packages permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>@babel/eslint-parser (the parser)</li>\n<li>eslint (the linter itself)</li>\n<li>eslint-config-react-app (ESLint configuration used by Create React App)</li>\n<li>eslint-plugin-import (little addon just for import statements)</li>\n<li>eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y (for amazing SEO results)</li>\n<li>eslint-plugin-react (for JSX)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Install them with <code class=\"language-text\">yarn add --dev &lt;packages></code></p>\n<h2 id=\"eslint-config\" style=\"position:relative;\">ESLint